verses.verse: To the chief <S%H5329>Musician<s%> <S%H5921>upon<s%> <S%H5058>Neginah,<s%> A Psalm of <S%H1732>David.<s%> <S%H8085>Hear<s%> my <S%H7440>cry,<s%> O <S%H430>God;<s%> attend <S%H7181>unto<s%> my <S%H8605>prayer.<s%>

From the <S%H4480>end<s%> <S%H7097><s%> of the <S%H776>earth<s%> will I <S%H7121>cry<s%> <S%H413>unto<s%> thee, when my <S%H3820>heart<s%> is <S%H5848>overwhelmed:<s%> <S%H5148>lead<s%> me to the <S%H6697>rock<s%> that is <S%H7311>higher<s%> <S%H4480>than<s%> I.
For <S%H3588><s%> thou hast <S%H1961>been<s%> a <S%H4268>shelter<s%> for me, and a <S%H5797>strong<s%> <S%H4026>tower<s%> <S%H4480>from<s%> <S%H6440><s%> the <S%H341>enemy.<s%>
I will <S%H1481>abide<s%> in thy <S%H168>tabernacle<s%> <S%H5769>forever:<s%> I will <S%H2620>trust<s%> in the <S%H5643>covert<s%> of thy <S%H3671>wings.<s%> <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>

For <S%H3588><s%> <S%H859>thou,<s%> O <S%H430>God,<s%> hast <S%H8085>heard<s%> my <S%H5088>vows:<s%> thou hast <S%H5414>given<s%> me the <S%H3425>heritage<s%> of those that <S%H3373>fear<s%> thy <S%H8034>name.<s%>
Thou wilt <S%H3254>prolong<s%> the <S%H4428>king's<s%> <S%H3117>life:<s%> <S%H5921><s%> <S%H3117><s%> and his <S%H8141>years<s%> <S%H3644>as<s%> many <S%H1755>generations.<s%> <S%H1755><s%>
He shall <S%H3427>abide<s%> <S%H6440>before<s%> <S%H430>God<s%> <S%H5769>forever:<s%> O <S%H4487>prepare<s%> <S%H2617>mercy<s%> and <S%H571>truth,<s%> which may <S%H5341>preserve<s%> him.
So <S%H3651><s%> will I sing <S%H2167>praise<s%> unto thy <S%H8034>name<s%> <S%H5703>forever,<s%> that I may <S%H3117>daily<s%> <S%H3117><s%> <S%H7999>perform<s%> my <S%H5088>vows.<s%>
